    "input": "What should happen before context compaction if exact tool outputs are still only in the chat?",
    "output": "Before the system performs any context\u2011compaction, you must copy the raw tool results (the exact JSON/text that the tool returned) and any decisions that were based on those results into a persistent archive (e.g., long\u2011term memory or a dedicated evidence store). In practice this means:\n\n1. **Capture the verbatim tool output** \u2013 take the `<tool_output \u2026>` block exactly as it appears, without trimming or re\u2011phrasing.\n2. **Record the associated decision** \u2013 store the rationale or action that followed the tool output (e.g., \u201cset_chart_state was queued\u201d, \u201ctrade size was calculated as 0.5\u202f% of equity\u201d).\n3. **Persist both items** \u2013 use a durable storage mechanism (`memory_add` or an evidence\u2011log) so they survive any later pruning of the chat history.\n4. **Mark them as evidence** \u2013 optionally tag the entry (e.g., `fact_type: \"evidence\"`) so that future audits can locate the original source quickly.\n\nOnly after these steps have been completed may the system safely discard or compress the surrounding conversational context, ensuring a complete audit trail remains available.",
